Sentencas: The effect of Ca2+ and Zn2+ cations substitution on the sinterability, thermal expansion and electrical properties of La0.85Sr0.15-xCaxCr1-yZnyO3 as solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) interconnect materials was investigated.
Titulo: Effect of Ca2+ and Zn2+ cations substitution on the properties of La0.85Sr0.15CrO3 as SOFC interconnect

Sentencas: The results showed that the bulk densities of La0.85Sr0.15-xCaxCrO3 increased with increasing Ca content and a maximum electrical conductivity value of 20.1 S/cm at 800 degrees C was obtained when x = 0.05.
Titulo: Effect of Ca2+ and Zn2+ cations substitution on the properties of La0.85Sr0.15CrO3 as SOFC interconnect

Sentencas: The transition metal Zn substituted in Cr-site further optimized the sinterability and increased the bulk density by 25% when Zn content was up to 0.09.
Titulo: Effect of Ca2+ and Zn2+ cations substitution on the properties of La0.85Sr0.15CrO3 as SOFC interconnect

Sentencas: The La0.85Sr0.1Ca0.05Cr0.91Zn0.09O3 sample exhibited an electrical conductivity of 21.5 S/cm at 800 degrees C and a thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) of 10.3 x 10(-6) K-1 (20-800 degrees C), which is compatible with that of 8 mol.%-Y2O3-stabilized-ZrO2 (8YSZ) electrolyte.
Titulo: Effect of Ca2+ and Zn2+ cations substitution on the properties of La0.85Sr0.15CrO3 as SOFC interconnect
